Project Name

KasiFit (working name)

One-Line Description

A gamified community health platform designed for South African township youth that encourages healthy habits through quests, streaks, rankings, community challenges, and local activity discovery.

The Problem Being Solved

Lifestyle diseases such as:

Hypertension
Diabetes
Obesity

are increasing among young people.

The problem is not a lack of information.

The problem is:

Poor motivation
Lack of accountability
Lack of community support
Lack of awareness of local physical activities

KasiFit aims to make healthy habits engaging and rewarding by using game mechanics similar to Strava, Duolingo, and fitness challenges.

Core Concept

Users complete daily health quests.

Completing quests earns:

XP
Streaks
Badges
Community points

The goal is to encourage long-term healthy behavior.

The app should feel like:

Strava
Duolingo
Habitica

combined into a simple health platform.

Target Audience

Primary:

South African township youth
Ages 15–35

Secondary:

Individuals living with:
Diabetes
Hypertension
Obesity
MVP Features
1. Authentication
Registration

Fields:

Full name
Username
Email
Password

Optional:

Profile photo
Health condition(s)
Login
Email + Password

Future:

Google login
Apple login
2. Onboarding

After registration:

User selects:

Health Goals

Examples:

Lose weight
Improve fitness
Manage diabetes
Manage hypertension
Build healthy habits
Interests

Examples:

Walking
Running
Soccer
Netball
Gym
Cycling

The selected goals influence quests.

3. Dashboard (Main Screen)

This is the most important screen.

Layout:

Top section:

Profile avatar

Current rank

Current streak

Example:

🔥 12 Day Streak
🥈 Silver Rank

Middle section:

Daily Quest Cards

Example:

Today's Quests

✅ Walk 3000 steps

⬜ Drink 2L water

⬜ Take medication

⬜ Healthy meal logged

Each quest:

progress indicator
XP reward

Bottom section:

Community standings

Example:

Mamelodi - 52,000 pts

Soshanguve - 48,000 pts

Tembisa - 44,000 pts
4. Health Quest System

This is the core feature.

Users receive:

Daily Quests

Examples:

Walk 3000 steps
Walk 5000 steps
Drink water
Take medication
Attend activity
Weekly Quests

Examples:

Complete 5 walks
Maintain streak
Join community event

Quest Completion Rewards

Each quest gives:

XP
Coins
Community points

Example:

Walk 3000 steps

Reward:

+50 XP
+10 Coins
5. Streak System

The most addictive feature.

Rules:

User must complete at least one quest daily.

Example:

Day 1

Streak = 1

Day 2

Streak = 2

Day 15

Streak = 15

Missing a day resets streak.

Visual:

Large flame icon.

Example:

🔥 23 Day Streak

This should be prominently displayed.

6. XP and Ranking System

Users gain XP.

Ranks:

Bronze

Silver

Gold

Platinum

Diamond

Community Champion

Example:

Bronze
0 - 999 XP

Silver
1000 - 2999 XP

Gold
3000 - 5999 XP

Users should always see:

Current XP

XP needed for next rank

Progress bar

7. Medication Verification

Users can set:

Medication name
Reminder time

Example:

Metformin

08:00 AM

Reminder notification appears.

User clicks:

"Verify Medication"

Camera opens.

User takes live picture.

The photo is submitted as proof.

For MVP:

Store image.

Mark medication quest completed.

Future:

AI verification.

8. Activity Tracking

MVP version:

User manually logs activity.

Examples:

Walk
Run
Soccer
Netball

Fields:

Activity Type

Duration

Distance

Future:

Google Fit integration.

Apple Health integration.

9. Local Activity Discovery

Purpose:

Promote real-world activity.

Users can browse:

Fun runs
Soccer tournaments
Netball tournaments
Community walks

Event Card:

5km Fun Walk

Saturday

Mamelodi

Free Entry

User can:

Join event
Save event

Completing event gives bonus XP.

10. Community Feed

Simple social feed.

Users post:

Achievement unlocked
Weight loss progress
Quest completion

Example:

Completed a 5km walk today 🔥

Interactions:

Like
Comment

Keep it lightweight.

Not another Facebook.

11. Community Challenges

Groups compete.

Example:

Monthly Challenge
Which township can earn the most health points?

Leaderboard:

Mamelodi
Soshanguve
Atteridgeville
Tembisa

Every completed quest contributes points.

